article.headline: Norfolk St. 66, Hampton 50
article.story: NORFOLK, Va. -- Michael Deloach had 15 points and five steals to lead Norfolk State to a 66-50 win over Hampton on Saturday night as the Spartans won two games in a row for the first time this season. Norfolk State (3-12, 2-2 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference), playing its first home game since Dec. 5, used a 22-4 run to lead 32-15 with 1:44 left in the first half of the Basketball Battle of the Bay. The Spartans increased their 33-22 halftime lead to 19 points with 1:04 left. Deloach, who was 7-for-16 from the floor, also paced Norfolk State with 25 points Monday night when the Spartans snapped their 11-game losing streak, 78-65 at Florida A&M. The Pirates (4-12, 1-3), who lost their second straight game, were led by Vincent Simpson with 13 points. Norfolk State had 23 turnovers but outshot Hampton 51 percent from the field (25-for-49) to 29 percent (18-for-62).
